  <text>
    <body>
      <div>
        <p><orgName ref="#BSU">Black Student Union</orgName> <choice><orig>representa­-tives</orig><reg>representatives</reg></choice><lb/>
who met with University <choice><orig>Pres-­ident</orig><reg>President</reg></choice><lb/>
<persName ref="#WE">Wilson H. Elkins</persName> Monday <choice><orig>con-­cerning</orig><reg>concerning</reg></choice><lb/>
their 14 demands said <choice><orig>yes-­terday</orig><reg>yesterday</reg></choice><lb/>
they were not satisfied with the<lb/>
discussion.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p><persName ref="#FH">Foster Hall,</persName> <orgName ref="#BSU">BSU</orgName> treasurer and<lb/>
one of three members who met with<lb/>
<persName ref="#WE">Elkins,</persName> said they will seek another<lb/>
meeting with <persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> tomorrow.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p><q>"If we don’t see any action on our<lb/>
demands, we will take our own <choice><orig>ac-­tion,”</orig><reg>action</reg></choice></q><lb/>
he added.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>The other two representatives who
met with <persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> were <orgName ref="#BSU">BSU</orgName> <choice><orig>Pres-­ident</orig><reg>President</reg></choice><lb/>
<persName ref="#TC">Terance Cooper</persName> and <persName ref="#CY"><choice><orig>Chrlss</orig><reg>Chriss</reg></choice><lb/>
Young.</persName><lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>During the 45-minute meeting, all<lb/>
but three of the demands were <choice><orig>dis-­cussed,</orig><reg>discussed</reg></choice><lb/>
Hall said. The original list<lb/>
of demands had been presented <choice><orig>Fri­-day</orig><reg>Friday</reg></choice><lb/>
to <persName ref="#WW">Walter B. Waetjen</persName>, vice <choice><orig>pres-­ident</orig><reg>president</reg></choice><lb/>
for administrative affairs.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p><persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> began by saying the demand<lb/>
that he and other members of the<lb/>
administration resign was <choice><orig>non-neg-­otiable,</orig><reg>non-negotioable</reg></choice><lb/>
according to <persName ref="#FH">Hall.</persName><lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>Some of the demands were be<lb/>­
yond his authority, <persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> added <choice><orig>ac-­cording</orig><reg>according</reg></choice><lb/>
to a University spokesman,<lb/>
and if he resigned he <q>‘‘wouldn’t be<lb/>
in a position to respond”</q> at all.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
       <p>The president said he had no <choice><orig>auth-­ority</orig><reg>authority</reg></choice><lb/>
to Intervene in the <orgName ref="#MSC">Maryland<lb/>
State College</orgName> Issue until the school<lb/>
comes under <orgName ref="#UMD">University</orgName> jurisdiction<lb/>
July 1.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p><orgName ref="#BSU">BSU</orgName> had demanded that the <orgName ref="#MSCP">181<lb/>
students arrested at <orgName ref="#MSC">the college</orgName></orgName> <choice><orig>rec­-ently</orig><reg>recently</reg></choice><lb/>
not be penalized for their <choice><orig>buil-­ding</orig><reg>building</reg></choice><lb/>
occupation action and that <choice><orig>col­-lege</orig><reg>college</reg></choice><lb/>
President <persName ref="#JW">John T. Williams</persName> be<lb/>
fired.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p><persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> also said he had no <choice><orig>in-­fluence</orig><reg>influence</reg></choice><lb/>
with the state to push for<lb/>
pay raises for campus classified<lb/>
workers, as <orgName ref="#BSU">BSU</orgName> had demanded, <persName ref="FH">Hall</persName><lb/>
said.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>
<persName ref="#WE">The president</persName> answered the demand<lb/>
for a change In the black studies <choice><orig>pro-­
gram</orig><reg>program</reg></choice><lb/>
to Include black community-<choice><orig>ori-­ented</orig><reg>oriented</reg></choice><lb/>
projects by saying the <choice><orig>Uni­-versity</orig><reg><orgName ref="#UMD">University</orgName></reg></choice><lb/>
<q>"does not have the <choice><orig>capabil-­ity</orig><reg>capability</reg></choice><lb/>
or presently the faculty to <choice><orig>ex-­tend</orig><reg>extend</reg></choice><lb/>
itself”</q> Into the community.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p><persName ref="#FH">Hall</persName> noted that the increase in funds<lb/>
for black studies, which <persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> said<lb/>
would be proportional to the Increase<lb/>
In the entire budget, was not accept<lb/>­
able to <orgName ref="#BSU">BSU</orgName> members.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p>To the demand that classes be <choice><orig>pro­-vided</orig><reg>provided</reg></choice><lb/>
for residents of nearby <settlement><choice><orig>Lake­-land,</orig><reg>Lakeland</reg></choice></settlement><lb/>
<persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> responded that classes<lb/>
are both possible and probable.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p>He said he would talk to faculty<lb/>
about It and requested <orgName ref="#BSU">BSU</orgName> to draw<lb/>
up a plan for using the adult <choice><orig>edu­-cation</orig><reg>education</reg></choice><lb/>
center for the classes.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p><persName ref="#FH">Hall</persName> said that plan and another<lb/>
one for including the children of<lb/>
campus service workers in the <choice><orig>Uni-­versity</orig><reg><orgName ref="#UMD">University</orgName></reg></choice><lb/>
kindergarten program would<lb/>
be submitted today.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p><persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> had Informed the <orgName ref="#BSU">BSU</orgName> <choice><orig>rep-­resentatives</orig><reg>representatives</reg></choice><lb/>
at the meeting that the<lb/>
kindergarten was open to all campus<lb/>
<sic>employes</sic>.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p>The demand that recruiting of black<lb/>
students and faculty be stepped up<lb/>
was answered with a statement by <choice><orig>El-­kins</orig><reg><persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName></reg></choice><lb/>
that the present program was<lb/>
sufficient.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p><persName ref="#FH">Hall</persName> contended, however, that the<lb/>
number of blacks has not increased<lb/>
substantially, although he said he<lb/>
would not have the exact figures <choice><orig>un-­til</orig><reg>until</reg></choice><lb/>
today.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p>one of the demands, that amnesty<lb/>
be granted to <persName type="unidentified">three black students</persName><lb/>
who were arested after a fight In<lb/>
<settlement>College Park</settlement> recently, had been<lb/>
turned over to <persName ref="#JM">J. Winston Martin,</persName><lb/>
vice president for student affairs,<lb/>
for Investigation shortly after the<lb/>
Incident happened.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p><persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> noted that the University<lb/>
does not have jurisdiction In such<lb/>
off-campus cases.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p><persName ref="#FH">Hall</persName> mentioned, however, that he<lb/>
has not heard from <persName ref="#JM">Martin</persName> since<lb/>
sometime before Easter vacation.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p>Regarding another demand, <persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName><lb/>
said it would be <q>“illegal”</q> to <choice><orig>reor­-ganize</orig><reg>reorganize</reg></choice><lb/>
the University structure to<lb/>
place control in the hands of students,
faculty and chosen administrators.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p>He said, however, that as soon as<lb/>
a human relations director is <choice><orig>appoin-­ted,</orig><reg>original,</reg></choice><lb/>
students could take their ideas<lb/>
for change to him. The director will<lb/>
be the vice chancellor, <persName ref="#WE">Elkins</persName> said.<lb/>
Both the director and the <choice><orig>chancel-­lor</orig><reg>chancellor</reg></choice><lb/>
have yet to be appointed.<lb/></p>
      </div>
      <div>
<p>The demand for free legal counsel<lb/>
for black students “made to suffer<lb/>
as a result of their political <choice><orig>activ-­ity”</orig><reg>activity"</reg></choice><lb/>
was satisfied when <orgName ref="#SGA">Student <choice><orig>Gov-­ernment</orig><reg>Government</reg></choice></orgName><lb/>
President <persName ref="#SR">Stu Robinson</persName> <choice><orig>of-fered</orig><reg>offered</reg></choice><lb/>
the use of the <orgName ref="#SGA">SGA</orgName> legal aid<lb/>
fund, which does not come from state<lb/>
funds, <persName ref="#FH">Hall</persName> said.<lb/></p>
      </div>
